songs.chartText:
1 Lord, he thought he'd make a man, 9 Firs' she took a little pull;
Dese bones gwine to rise again; Dese bones gwine to rise again;
Made him out of mud and a little bit of sand, Den she filled her apron full.
Dese bones gwine to rise again. Dese bones gwine to rise again.
Refrain: 10 Adam he come prowlin' roun';
I know it, 'deed I know it, Dese bones gwine to rise again;
Dese bones gwine to rise again. Spied dem peelin's on de groun'.

2 "Adam, Adam, where art thou?"

Dese bones gwine to rise again; 11 Den he took a little slice;
"Here, Marse Lord, I'se comin' down." Dese bones gwine to rise again;
Dese bones gwine to rise again. Smack his lips an' said 'twas nice.

3 Thought he'd make a woman too;
Dese bones gwine to rise again; 12 Lord, he spoke with a mighty voice.
Didn't know 'xactly what to do. Dese bones gwine to rise again;
Dese bones gwine to rise again. Shook de heavens to de joists.

4 Took a rib from Adam's side;
Dese bones gwine to rise again; 13 "Adam! Adam! Where are thou?"

Made Miss Eve for to be his bride. Dese bones gwine to rise again;
Dese bones gwine to rise again. "Yes, Marse Lord, I'se a-comin' now."

5 Put 'em in a garden rich an' fair;
Dese bones gwine to rise again; 14 "You et my apples, I believe?"

Tole 'em to eat what they found dere. Dese bones gwine to rise again;
Dese bones gwine to rise again. "Not me, Lord, but I 'spec 'twas Eve.'

6 To one tall tree dey mus' not go;
Dere mus' de fruit forever grow.

15 Lord den rose up in his wrath;
Tole 'em beat it down de path.

7 Ol Miss Eve come a-walkin' roun';
Spied dat tree all loaded down.

16 "Out of my garden you mus' git,"
"For you an' me has got to quit.

">

8 Sarpent he came roun' de trunk.

Dese bones gwine to rise again; Refrain:
At Miss Eve his eye he wunk. I know it, 'deed I know it,
Dese bones gwine to rise again. Dese bones gwine to rise again.

Good San broth-er, good-bye, broth-er, If I don't see you more;

Now God bless you, now God bless you, If I don't' see you more.

2 We part in de body, but we meet in de spirit,
If I don't see you more;
We'll meet in de heaben, in de blessed kingdom,
If I don't see you more.

3 So good-bye brother, good-bye sister,
If I don't see you more;
Now God bless you, now God bless you,
If I don't see you more.
